ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you are interested in learning about membranes you should take this class.

I would definitely recommend this course to anyone who plans on studying membranes, membrane proteins, membrane dynamics, or any other field that relates to membrane biology. The course was enjoyable and engaging.
Great survey class for students interested in membrane biophysics.

It was a great course and you will learn a lot about membranes. The topics were varied which made the classes interesting: history of membranes, lipid bilayer basics, ion channels, structural approaches to view membranes, etc.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This topic was definitely outside my general field of study but it was good to branch out and get a more broad knowledge of science
I found this course immensely helpful for my dissertation research on a membrane protein. I knew very little about membrane dynamics or general transporter behavior prior to this course
This course was relevant to my study because I am studying localization of a protein that associates with a membrane protein. I learned a lot about membranes in their course.
